  "text": "The paper by Josef Finsterer and Gianni Sorarù entitled \"Onset manifestations of spinal and bulbar muscular atrophy (Kennedy disease)\" [CITATION_1] addresses open questions in the clinical profiling of SBMA. There is indeed a critical need to establish which clinical symptoms better define the onset of disease and whether the age of onset is directly correlated to the length of the CAG expansion when non-motor symptoms are taken into account. A meta-analysis allowed the authors to establish that non-motor symptoms develop before motor symptoms, and when considered in establishing the age of onset, this becomes independent of CAG repeat length. These results imply that non-motor symptoms are important aspects of the disease that should be considered in the estimation of age of onset and disease course. Because the efficacy of treatment may be inversely correlated with disease duration, it is critical to establish unifying criteria to assess disease onset based not only on classical motor symptoms but also on the parameters described in this work.",
